 uncovers the artistic representation of plants in our lives and in the natu
 ral world. It features objects from the Gregg Museum of Art & Design Collec
 tion that depict the roles of plants from nourishment and communal living t
 o the scientific study of human health. The House of Ideas offers a relaxin
 g room for botanical sketching and a self-guided tour of the museum’s garde
 n.
