BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State Gregg Museum of Art & Design
CATEGORIES:Community Events,Performances
DESCRIPTION:Join the Gregg Museum of Art & Design for an unforgettable even
 ing on the museum's lawn with Alexis Raeana. Raeana's Indigenous soul sound
  blends southern flair\, powerful storytelling and a dynamic mix of origina
 l songs and crowd-favorite covers. Raeana captivates audiences with a voice
  that feels both revolutionary and deeply familiar. She crafts southern-sou
 l melodies that electrify and resonate. The music video for her debut singl
 e\, Keep My Memory\, raises awareness for missing and murdered Indigenous w
 omen and earned the Lumbee Film of the Year at the Lumbee Film Festival.\n\
 nBring a blanket and/or lawn chairs\, relax under the stars and enjoy an ev
 ening of music\, storytelling and community with Raeana and her band. Expec
 t a rich musical experience featuring saxophone\, acoustic guitar\, bass an
 d layered backing vocals\, bringing together an immersive performance that 
 is truly more than music.
DTEND:20260502T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260327T030132Z
DTSTART:20260501T230000Z
GEO:35.784762;-78.661636
LOCATION:Gregg Museum of Art & Design\, Front Lawn
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Music on the Gregg Museum Lawn With Alexis Raeana
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51949188916666
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/music-on-the-gregg-museum-lawn-with-ale
 xis-raeana
END:VEVENT
